    • preOrderTraverse

      public void preOrderTraverse(BinaryTree.Node<E> node, int depth, StringBuilder sb)
      If the node is null, append "null" to the string builder. Otherwise, append the node's data to the string builder, then recursively call the function on the left and right children
      Parameters:
      node - the node to start at
      depth - the depth of the current node
      sb - a StringBuilder object that will be used to build the string that represents the tree.
